The infographic titled “Digital Literacy for Students” was designed using Canva to spread awareness about essential digital skills among students. The design is divided into three main sections: What is Digital Literacy, Safe Internet Practices, and Professional Online Presence.
The first section explains digital literacy as the ability to use digital tools safely, effectively, and responsibly. It highlights key aspects such as online skills, critical thinking, and cyber awareness. The second section focuses on safe internet practices, including using strong passwords, identifying phishing scams, keeping software updated, and thinking before clicking on links.
The third section emphasizes the importance of building a professional online presence by creating platforms like LinkedIn and GitHub, sharing achievements, and networking professionally.
The infographic uses a clean layout with engaging visuals and contrasting colors to make the information easy to understand and visually appealing. One interesting aspect of creating this design was organizing complex ideas into simple visual points, while maintaining clarity and readability for students.
